CBRE & Property Solutions are pleased to bring Lots 10-19 Fife Place to market for sale. 

- Lot sizes from 1,127sqm* to 1,499sqm*
- Optimal layout flexibility with the ability to combine and create a larger space.
- Excellent opportunity to develop, occupy or invest
- Each lot is fully serviced and ready for immediate construction 
- Ideally located with easy access to the Hume Highway interchange & Goulburn town Centre, Coles DC & Bunnings.
- Positioned one hour from Canberra and two hours from Sydney
- Direct access to the Melbourne-Sydney railway line 
- Zoned B6 Enterprise Corridor

CBRE as exclusive agents are delighted to offer this approved residential land subdivision to market. The site offers developers an opportunity to capitalise on a growth region with a high demand and undersupply of housing lots. 

Key development highlights: 

- Stage 1 approval for 205 residential lots with further potential to expand to 307 lots (STCA)
- Flexible R2 Low Density Residential & RU6 zoning
- Strong market fundamentals – extremely low residential vacancy rate of 0.71% 
- Large site of 41.24 hectares (102 acres) 
- Dual street access to Marys Mount Road & Middle Arm Road
- To be sold together or separately with rural land holding at Biala - 113.6 hectares (280 acres)

The Hills Grandview Estate in conjunction with Sapphire Road, Biala will be sold by way of Expression of Interest. The sales process will close Wednesday, 3 March 2021 by 4PM. Offers are to be submitted via email to the exclusive agents at CBRE.

This large parcel of land offers an opportunity to secure one of the most significant industrial opportunities within Goulburn with direct frontage to Hume Highway and rail siding to the main Southern Railway Line. Alternatively the property offers three individual rural lots perfect for agricultural purposes or even a hobby farm.

• Three separate blocks on the edge of Goulburn City
• Each block comprises a dwelling / improvements
• Total area: 167.4* hectares
• Zoned IN1 (General Industrial)
• DA approval for an intermodal industrial estate with 26 allotments ranging in size from 30,000sqm* to 100,000sqm* (plus rail siding)
• Suitable for rural residential or industrial subdivision
• Lots for sale individually or in-one-line

EOI: Closing Tuesday 9th September 2014
